ZH: 他长时间的重复做同一件事，导致他的手指麻木了。
EN: He repeated the same action for a long time, causing his fingers to go numb.

ZH: 这个冬天太冷，我都感到麻木了。
EN: This winter is so cold, I feel numb all over.

ZH: 她站了很久，腿都麻木了。
EN: She stood for a long time, her legs went numb.

ZH: 长时间的使用电子设备会使手指麻木。
EN: Long-term use of electronic devices can make your fingers go numb.

ZH: 整天坐在办公室里工作，我感到腰都麻木了。
EN: Working in the office all day, my back goes numb.

ZH: 他的脚被细绳绑住了，很快就麻木了。
EN: His feet were tied up with a rope and quickly went numb.

ZH: 大量饮酒会导致身体麻木。
EN: Drinking alcohol in large quantities can cause numbness in the body.

ZH: 这种药可以减轻疼痛，但可能会使你的皮肤麻木。
EN: This medicine can relieve pain, but it may cause numbness in your skin.

ZH: 他躺在沙发上看电视，腿慢慢麻木了。
EN: He lay on the couch watching TV, and his legs gradually went numb.

ZH: 长时间保持同一姿势会导致肌肉麻木。
EN: Maintaining the same position for a long time can cause muscle numbness.

ZH: 在山上远足时，我的手被冻得麻木了。
EN: My hands went numb from the cold while hiking in the mountains.

ZH: 在手术中，局部麻醉会使某个部位麻木。
EN: During the surgery, local anesthesia will numb a specific area.

ZH: 她在手术期间被完全麻醉了，一切感觉都消失了。
EN: She was completely numb during the surgery, and all feelings disappeared.

ZH: 这种药物的副作用之一是麻木感。
EN: One of the side effects of this medication is a numb sensation.

ZH: 长时间盯着电脑屏幕会使眼睛麻木。
EN: Staring at a computer screen for a long time can make your eyes go numb.

ZH: 久坐会导致臀部麻木。
EN: Sitting for a long time can lead to numbness in the buttocks.

ZH: 他们在夜晚的风中等了很久，手指都麻木了。
EN: They waited in the wind for a long time at night, and their fingers went numb.

ZH: 长时间低头看手机会使脖子麻木。
EN: Looking down at your phone for a long time can make your neck go numb.

ZH: 手术后，她的脸部因麻醉药物而麻木。
EN: After the surgery, her face was numb due to anesthesia.

ZH: 暴露在寒冷的环境中会使你的身体麻木。
EN: Exposing yourself to a cold environment can make your body go numb.
